The defendant Seth W. Keller was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Take and Drive Vehicle w/o Consent, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(2).

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. miscConds.notes: Defendant shall submit to a DNA sample at the Taylor County Sheriff's Department.  The restitution and costs shall be paid directly to the Taylor County Clerk of Court at the rate of $100.00 a month beginning July 22, 2022.  Failure to pay may result in a civil judgment being entered against you, tax intercept, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant shall have no contact with the victim,  D.J.T.

Defendant shall write a letter of apology to the victim, D.J.T. dues within 30 days of sentencing and preapproved by probation.  Defendant shall undergo counseling as deemed appropriate by probation.  Defendant shall pay supervision fees as ordered by the Department of Corrections. If probation is ordered and ultimately revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA and comply with any treatment recommendations.
